parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident. It can also result in costly repairs, including engine replacement.
symptoms: The engine light comes on
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine makes a loud noise or vibration
the vehicle shakes or bucks while driving
the timing chain tensioner fails
and the engine oil leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain tensioner can cause the timing chain to skip or break, leading to engine failure and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: The engine light comes on
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine makes a loud noise or vibration
the vehicle shakes or bucks while driving
and the timing chain fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause a loss of power and potentially lead to an accident, and can also result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine light comes on
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine makes a loud noise or vibration
the vehicle shakes or bucks while driving
and the timing chain or tensioner fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Melted Fuse Box
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause multiple exterior lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Multiple exterior lights
including headlights
brake lights
and turn signals
malfunction or fail to operate; warning messages appear on the dashboard; fuse box is melted or overheated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress through the sunroof can cause electrical issues, mold, and water damage, leading to safety hazards and costly repairs.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the sunroof; water accumulates in the footwell; mold and mildew growth; electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Headlight failure can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Headlights malfunction or fail to operate; bulbs need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turn signal malfunction can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: Turn signals malfunction or fail to operate; left turn indicators flash when turning right.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine and timing chain failure can cause the engine to stall or fail, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: Engine hesitates or stalls; timing chain slips or jumps time; engine damage or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The power steering light illuminates
the steering wheel shakes or wobbles violently
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering functionality
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The power steering light illuminates intermittently
the steering wheel shakes or wobbles violently intermittently
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn intermittently
the vehicle loses power steering functionality intermittently
the steering wheel locks up intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Assist/Rack and Pinion Gear Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering assist or rack and pinion gear can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The power steering light illuminates
the steering wheel shakes or wobbles violently
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering functionality
the steering wheel locks up.
